{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487048","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487048"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:55:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:55:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"239"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"239","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/239"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.04,0.11,0.44,0.28]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"239"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61051"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"239","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/239"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"239"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46499"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"316"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"1243"},{"type":"tags","id":"2259"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19195"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42035"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42984"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44568"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44748"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61051","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61051"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-month history of left shoulder pain radiating down his left arm. The pain has persisted despite physiotherapy and regular analgesia. He has a medical history of coronary artery disease with stent insertion five years ago. His medications include clopidogrel and aspirin. He is a current smoker with a 45 pack-year history and reports a chronic, non-productive cough.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is wasting of the intrinsic muscles of the left hand. The left shoulder has full range of movement without localised tenderness. Neck flexion is limited but lateral rotation is normal. The remainder of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["MRI left shoulder","X-ray left shoulder","Nerve conduction studies","Chest X-ray","X-ray cervical spine"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features highly suspicious for a Pancoast tumour (superior sulcus tumour): shoulder pain, intrinsic hand muscle wasting, and significant smoking history. Given these findings and the high risk of lung cancer, imaging of the chest is essential before pursuing other investigations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial investigation for suspected lung cancer. While it may not always show early superior sulcus tumours clearly, it is readily available and can identify obvious apical lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMRI left shoulder\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as the initial investigation as there are no localising signs in the shoulder itself, and it would not identify the likely underlying cause of symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EX-ray left shoulder\u003C/strong\u003E would similarly be low yield given the normal shoulder examination and would miss the likely thoracic pathology.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENerve conduction studies\u003C/strong\u003E might confirm a brachial plexopathy but would not identify the underlying cause, which is the priority in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EX-ray cervical spine\u003C/strong\u003E might show degenerative changes explaining the reduced neck flexion, but given the concerning features for malignancy, investigation of the thorax takes precedence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPancoast tumours typically present with shoulder pain and neurological symptoms due to involvement of the brachial plexus, sympathetic chain, or vertebral bodies. The combination of significant smoking history, chronic cough, and upper limb neurological symptoms should prompt chest imaging before pursuing other investigations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pancoast tumour should be suspected in smokers presenting with shoulder pain and hand muscle wasting.","Chest X-ray is the initial investigation of choice for suspected lung cancer, even when presenting with apparently musculoskeletal symptoms.","Neurological symptoms in the upper limb may be the first presentation of an apical lung tumour."],"references":["Marulli G, Battistella L, Mammana M, Calabrese F, Rea F. Superior sulcus tumors (Pancoast tumors).\u00a0Ann Transl Med.\u00a02016 Jun;4(12):239. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27429965/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46499"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"239"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/46499"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-14T20:49:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-14T20:50:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"239"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61051"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"ta